{"actor":"Chris Williams","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-03T17:35:10Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":64,"issue_id":"ss-0dh.6","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"ss-0dh.6\",\"title\":\"Shared infrastructure: Skill discovery \\u0026 frontmatter parsing library\",\"description\":\"## Overview\\nMultiple planned commands (budget, verify, lint, policy, test) need to discover installed skills and parse their SKILL.md frontmatter. The audit command already does this, but the logic is embedded in the audit orchestrator. Extract shared skill discovery and frontmatter parsing into reusable modules that all commands can consume.\\n\\n## Current State\\n- `audit/index.ts` discovers skill files and parses frontmatter\\n- `audit/extractors/` extract packages, commands, URLs from skill content\\n- This logic is coupled to the audit pipeline\\n\\n## What to Extract\\n1. **Skill Discovery** — Find all SKILL.md files in a directory (recursive), respecting .gitignore\\n2. **Frontmatter Parsing** — Parse YAML frontmatter from SKILL.md files into typed objects\\n3. **Section Parsing** — Split a skill into sections by markdown headings (needed by budget for per-section token counts, by verify for structural diff)\\n4. **Content Extraction** — The extractors (packages, commands, URLs) should be importable by any command\\n\\n## Design Principle\\nFrom CLAUDE.md: 'This extractor/checker/reporter pattern is the template for all future commands.' The shared infrastructure enables this by making extractors reusable.\\n\\n## Proposed Location\\n```\\nsrc/\\n  shared/\\n    discovery.ts      # Find SKILL.md files\\n    frontmatter.ts    # Parse YAML frontmatter\\n    sections.ts       # Parse markdown into sections\\n    types.ts          # Shared types (SkillFile, Frontmatter, Section)\\n```\\n\\nOr refactor audit/extractors to be importable from a common path.\\n\\n## Acceptance Criteria\\n- [ ] Skill discovery works independently of audit command\\n- [ ] Frontmatter parsing returns typed objects\\n- [ ] Section parsing handles nested headings\\n- [ ] Audit command still works after refactor (no behavior change)\\n- [ ] All extractors importable from outside audit/\\n- [ ] Unit tests for discovery, parsing, and section splitting\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"voodootikigod@gmail.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T18:46:58Z\",\"created_by\":\"Chris Williams\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T18:46:58Z\"}"}
